A path in a dim light
that I have to walk myself.

Rain falling from my lips,
the most cleanest of all.

Dissany,
esperance in isolation.
Cold hands clutching at
something that is gone.

Her,
dressed in black.

A warmth
surrounding me
when I saw her eyes
sparkling.


_______________
Name    Fatigue
Artist  Heretoir
Album   Heretoir
